description: During a mist net bird capture project I observed the Hibiscus growing along an inlet of the Stone Lakes Wildlife Refuge. Mike Brady, Biologist for the refuge at the time, confirmed the identification. This specimen was growing wild.

Paul Euwer was surfing when the attack occured.
Source: McCosker, J.E. and R.N. Lea. 2006. White Shark Attacks Upon Humans in California and Oregon, 1993-2003. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences 57(17):479-501. (230)
